@startuml current_001_component_layers
title UC Life Sim — current component layers (HEAD)

' Rule: data flows DOWN. Upward edges are violations.
' This diagram shows ONLY the layering rule + the edges that cross more
' than one layer or violate it. Per-layer file inventories are in notes,
' not nested components — keeping the graph readable.

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam defaultFontName "Inter, sans-serif"
skinparam linetype ortho
top to bottom direction

package "config\n*.json5 → loaders, read once at boot" as L_CFG  #f3f6fa
package "data\nstatic content (scenes, jobs, ships, …)" as L_DATA #f3f6fa
package "procgen\npure, seeded — roads → blocks → cells" as L_PROC #eef5ee
package "ecs\nkoota traits + Map<SceneId, World>" as L_ECS  #fff8ec
package "ai\nmistreevous BT (trees + agent)" as L_AI   #fff3e6
package "sim\nclock, scene, loop, ship, transition" as L_SIM  #fff3e6
package "systems\n28 files (vitals, work, npc, combat, …)" as L_SYS  #fff3e6
package "save\nidb-keyval + superjson" as L_SAVE #f0e6ff
package "render\npixi + sprite + portrait" as L_REND #e9f3ff
package "ui\nReact DOM + zustand stores" as L_UI   #e9f3ff
package "boot\nmain.tsx :: ScopedRoot" as L_BOOT #ffffff

' --- intended (downward) dependency direction ---
L_CFG  --> L_DATA
L_DATA --> L_PROC
L_DATA --> L_ECS
L_PROC --> L_ECS
L_ECS  --> L_SIM
L_AI   --> L_SYS
L_SIM  --> L_SYS
L_SYS  --> L_REND
L_SYS  --> L_SAVE
L_REND --> L_UI
L_BOOT --> L_REND
L_BOOT --> L_UI

' --- violations / concerns (red) ---
L_SAVE -[#red]-> L_SIM : (V) save calls stop/startLoop\n+ per-system reset hooks
L_SIM  -[#red]-> L_SAVE : (V) loop calls tryAutosave\non day-rollover / hyperspeed-start
L_BOOT -[#red]-> L_SYS  : (V) __uclife__ DEV surface\nreaches ~10 subsystems

note right of L_SYS
  Module-level singletons in:
  combat, population, relations,
  npc (buckets), activeZone, vitals,
  stress, supplyDrain, spaceSim,
  engagement.
  Not per-world. Works only because
  the world count is fixed and small.
end note

note right of L_REND
  render/ has its own internal seam:
   - Game.tsx + ground/PixiGroundRenderer
     (ECS snapshot → pixi)
   - sprite/ (LPC composer, anim ticker)
   - portrait/ (FC pregmod port — opaque
     core, UC owns bridge + adapter)
  See 005_render_flow + 006_portrait_pipeline.
end note

@enduml
